# QR Generation Flow

## Core Workflow

The QR generation follows a strict 3-step process:

### Step 1: Template Selection
- User clicks on payment template from [frontend/app/(app)/overview/](mdc:frontend/app/(app)/overview/)
- Template contains only data (amount, description, IBAN)
- NO pre-generated QR codes stored

### Step 2: Dynamic Generation

1. **Generate Unique Variable Symbol**
   ```typescript
   const generateQRTransaction = async (template: PaymentTemplate) => {
     const variableSymbol = generateVariableSymbol();
   ```

2. **Call PHP QR Service**
   ```typescript
     const qrData = await fetch('/api/qr-service', {
       method: 'POST',
       body: JSON.stringify({
         iban: template.iban,
         amount: template.amount,
         description: template.description,
         variableSymbol
       })
     });
   ```

3. **Save Transaction Record**
   ```typescript
     const transaction: GeneratedTransaction = {
       templateId: template.id,
       templateName: template.name,
       amount: template.amount,
       variableSymbol,
       qrData: qrData.qrString,
       generatedAt: new Date(),
       status: 'generated'
     };
     await saveTransaction(transaction);
   };
   ```

### Step 3: Display QR Code

Components should follow this pattern:

```typescript
<QRGenerationFlow>
  {loading && <LoadingSpinner>Generating QR...</LoadingSpinner>}
  {qrReady && (
    <QRDisplay>
      <QRCode value={qrData} size={300} />
      <h2>€{amount}</h2>
      <p>{templateName}</p>
      <small>VS: {variableSymbol}</small>
    </QRDisplay>
  )}
</QRGenerationFlow>
```

## PHP QR Service Integration

The [qr-service/](mdc:qr-service) handles BySquare standard generation:

```php
$payment = new QrPayment(new IBAN($input['iban']));
$payment->setAmount((float)$input['amount']);
$payment->setComment($input['description']);
$payment->setVariableSymbol($input['variableSymbol']);
$qrString = $payment->getQrString();
```

## Expected Timing
- Generation time: <2 seconds (acceptable UX trade-off)
- Success rate: >99%
- Each QR is unique and trackable
